br.com.summa.sol.data

Class ListTopN<E extends Comparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.com.summa.sol.data.ListTopN<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TopN<E>, Serializable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>

    public class ListTopN<E extends Comparable<E>>
extends Object
implements TopN<E>
    A generic collection strictly limited to size N. If more than N elements are added, it will keep the greatest N elements only, discarding the others.

    Duplicate elements are allowed. For 2 arbitrary elements x and y such that x.compareTo(y) == 0, the oldest element in this collection will be treated as greater.

    This collection is optimized for small values of N (typically obtaining the "top5" or "top10" elements from a large set), keeping at most N elements stored in a LinkedList. For much larger values of N, use TreeTopN instead.
    Author:
    Einar Saukas
